SENATE BILL 325
By Massey
HOUSE BILL 455
By Hurt
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4;
Title 56 and Title 71, relative to autism spectrum
disorders.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 4-3-2711(h), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
(8) Submit an annual report by February 1 of each year to the senate health and
welfare committee and the committee in the house of representatives with subject matter
jurisdiction over health-related issues that details, at a minimum, the council's findings,
progress on the comprehensive statewide plan and system of care, and
recommendations for legislation.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
